 # Changelog
 
+## 2026-07-17 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S6-P03-T075 (Shadow topic-acceleration & central->local diffusion prediction; SHADOW)
+
+- Seventy-fifth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program. Two PREDEFINED pilot targets over the 2016+ event chain, each with a DISTINCT fixture (not clones): ACCEL-PILOT (will a research topic accelerate within 90 days?, base rate ~0.5) and DIFFUSION-A0-A1 (will a central A0 policy diffuse to a province A1 within 180 days?, base rate ~0.6). Each prediction conditions on a leading net support signal (support - counter, e.g. how many A1 provinces already echo the A0 policy minus superseding central events); the conditional model beats an unconditional base-rate baseline over three time-safe rolling windows whose validation is deliberately NOISY (carries impurities, so the model is imperfect and wins on aggregate not by construction), and every surfaced statement is a hedged probability -- no deterministic tone. release_mode SHADOW; predictions are computed in the dev/shadow environment only, the production worker/cron/data untouched, 0 cloud cost, DIR-007 unaffected, and the realtime build is unchanged. New tool arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/tools/diffusion_predictor.py: PREDEFINED_TARGETS (pilot + horizon), is_predefined (refuses a post-hoc target), fit_model (P(outcome | net-signal bucket) with Laplace shrinkage), predict (conditional, clamped strictly inside (0,1)), baseline_predict (unconditional base rate), rolling_backtest (reuses the T072 split + no-time-crossing, refuses a non-predefined target, per-window model-vs-baseline Brier + beats_all), phrase / assert_no_deterministic_tone (rejects a range of certainty markers and over-confident 0/1 probabilities), lead_time. Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/evidence/ADP-S6-P03-T075/: diffusion_predictor_report.json, known_gaps.md, and adversarial_review.md (review CONFIRMED_SOUND after a HOLE_FOUND on a vacuous control was fixed). Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S6-P03-T075/test-results/diffusion_predictor_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0), the verifier re-deriving each window's Brier with its own formula: three windows beat the baseline for both pilots (ACCEL 0.163/0.179/0.161 vs 0.250/0.258/0.250; DIFFUSION 0.169/0.146/0.137 vs 0.278/0.262/0.257 -- distinct profiles), with a REAL feature-ablation control (signal-blinded cases collapse the model exactly onto the baseline, ties, does not beat) and a corrupted-signal probe (inverting the validation signal degrades the model to 0.46-0.56, far worse than baseline) proving the win comes from the support/counter signal not the harness; the targets and horizon are predefined (a post-hoc target is refused by both is_predefined and rolling_backtest); and no deterministic tone (all surfaced probabilities strictly inside (0,1), and the gate rejects certainty phrasing and 0/1 probabilities). Realtime not regressed (no production deploy, live build b189d3cc0703 == T040). Cost (unknown != 0): production new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0, recurring cloud 0 (SHADOW dev env). Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
+
 ## 2026-07-17 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S6-P03-T074 (Shadow source-silence prediction; SHADOW)
 
 - Seventy-fourth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program (opens S6-P03). Predicts whether an official source's current quiet is abnormal (it should have published by now) or normal (within its cadence), and distinguishes abnormal source silence from a collection failure (our fetcher broke). release_mode SHADOW; predictions are computed in the dev/shadow environment only, the production worker/cron/data untouched, 0 cloud cost, DIR-007 unaffected, and the realtime build is unchanged. New tool arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/tools/silence_predictor.py: cadence (median inter-publication interval + MAD), simple_cycle_overdue (the baseline: overdue if the gap exceeds the median interval), classify (the model: a fetch error -> collection_failure; otherwise abnormal only if the gap exceeds median + k*MAD, a robust allowance for the source's own variability; returns normal/abnormal_silence/collection_failure), and evaluate (scores the model AND the baseline on the same labeled truth: accuracy, false-alarm rate, human value). Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/evidence/ADP-S6-P03-T074/: silence_predictor_report.json, known_gaps.md, and adversarial_review.md (review CONFIRMED_SOUND). Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S6-P03-T074/test-results/silence_predictor_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0): the model beats the simple publication-cycle baseline (accuracy 1.0 vs 0.667, false-alarm rate 0.0 vs 0.5, human value 4 vs 3) because its robust threshold does not false-alarm on a naturally-variable source and its fetch-error signal distinguishes a collection failure the baseline calls source silence; false alarms and human value are quantified numbers from the outcomes; and the model classifies a fetch failure as collection_failure while the cadence-only baseline cannot, and still catches a genuinely-abnormal silence on a variable source (it is not over-conservative). Realtime not regressed (no production deploy, live build b189d3cc0703 == T040). Cost (unknown != 0): production new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0, recurring cloud 0 (SHADOW dev env). Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
